as man<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter"> Lord Bolingbroke had al&s;o
&s;ome reputation for me+taphy&s;ical inquiry; his friends extolled his
&s;agacity on that head; and the public were willing enough t<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter"> acquie&s;ce in their opinion; his fame
therefore migh<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter"> have continued to
