<P>Sir Robert Walpole, who is to make the principa<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter"> figure in the pre&s;ent reign, had, from low
begin+nings, rai&s;ed him&s;elf to the head of the trea&s;ury<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter"> Strongly attached to the hou&s;e of
